Sentencas: Cation transport behavior, diffusion and interface reaction were investigated for La0.8Sr0.2CoO3 (LSC) and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 (LSF) perovskite cathodes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Cation transport behavior in SOFC cathode materials of La0.8Sr0.2CoO3 and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 with perovskite structure

Sentencas: Diffusion couples between two perovskite pellets were annealed around SOFC operating temperatures such as 1071 K, 1175 K, 1279 K and 1379 K. Mass transfer of the iron component from the LSF into the LSC was clearly observed by energy dispersed X-ray analysis (EDX) and secondary ion mass spectrometry (SIMS).
Titulo: Cation transport behavior in SOFC cathode materials of La0.8Sr0.2CoO3 and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 with perovskite structure

Sentencas: At the interface, the precipitation of CoFe2O4 spinel phase was observed on the LSF side.
Titulo: Cation transport behavior in SOFC cathode materials of La0.8Sr0.2CoO3 and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 with perovskite structure

Sentencas: On the LSC side interface, Sr-rich thin layer was observed; iron component difftised through the CoFe2O4 and the Sr-rich thin layer at high temperature.
Titulo: Cation transport behavior in SOFC cathode materials of La0.8Sr0.2CoO3 and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 with perovskite structure

Sentencas: The grain boundary diffusion of iron was faster than bulk diffusion.
Titulo: Cation transport behavior in SOFC cathode materials of La0.8Sr0.2CoO3 and La0.8Sr0.2FeO3 with perovskite structure
